      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LARRIKIN PIONEER (6) comes off an average run last start when seventh at Wentworth Park over 520m behind Zipping Kayli (30.96) in a Grade 5. Speedy beginner who can find the front despite the tricky draw. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. SANDRA KEEPING (2) had been in super honest form hitting the frame two times on end before finishing fourth (31.05) at this track last time. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. A big run wouldn't surprise. SHE'S VICIOUS (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 18.01 beating Mulwee Princess. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Bold showing expected again. FOOLS RUSH IN (8) has top-three aspirations after placing last time.",
